  .container
    .row.gray.fading.padding-top
      .col-md-6.col-12
        h2 The Facts
        p
          | Burning fossil fuels while traveling creates CO2, which is one of the greenhouse gasses that contribute to
          a(href='https://climate.nasa.gov/causes/')
                  |  climate change.
        p
          | In 2018 alone, flights around the world
          a(href='https://www.atag.org/facts-figures.html')
                  |  produced 895 million tons of CO2.
        p
          | Road based transportation is responsible for up to
          a(href='https://www.who.int/sustainable-development/transport/health-risks/air-pollution/en/')
                  |  30% of particulate emissions, which is a kind of emission that bypasses the natural defences of humans and animals.
        p
          | According to a 2010-2015 study,
          a(href='https://theicct.org/publications/health-impacts-transport-emissions-2010-2015')
                  |  tailpipe emissions lead to ~361,000 premature deaths in 2010, and ~385,000 premature deaths in 2015.
      .col-md-6.col-12
        h2 What Can You Do?
        p
          | You can reduce your impact on the world by taking a look at what you're doing wrong and comparing it to others.
        p
          | Take a page out of someone else's book by looking at what they've done right, and check out how everyone is doing overall.
        p
          | Get going on reducing your negative impact by
          a(href='http://www.dnrec.delaware.gov/dwhs/info/Pages/OzonePublicTrans.aspx')
                  |  trying out transit,
          |  reducing your amount of flights, and taking up walking and cycling.
        p
          | Check out
          a(href='https://en.reset.org/act/reduce-your-ecological-footprint-0')
                  |  more ways
          |  to reduce your negative impact.
